cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a likely category as the paper deals with scheduling tasks in a microprocessor system, which can be seen as a parallel computing system. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses thermal management at the operating systems level, which involves control of the system. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possible category as the paper deals with scheduling tasks on a microprocessor, which is a hardware component. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is a possible category as the paper deals with a relatively new technique for microprocessor thermal management. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category as the paper discusses maximizing the throughput of the system.
